# apps/medusa's `medusa build` bundles its admin dashboard with Vite,
# which resolves each Medusa admin-extension package (@medusajs/dashboard,
# @medusajs/draft-order/admin, etc.) via plain Node resolution from
# apps/medusa's own node_modules — that only works if those packages
# are hoisted to a place Node's default (non-pnpm-symlink-aware)
# resolution can find, hence this narrow hoist pattern rather than a
# blanket `shamefully-hoist=true`.
#
# Deliberately NOT hoisting react/react-dom here (an earlier version of
# this file did): apps/web and packages/ui now depend on React 19 while
# apps/medusa's own admin bundle depends on React 18 — Medusa already
# resolves its own copy correctly via its own node_modules symlink
# without needing it hoisted, and hoisting either version to the root
# risks some part of the Next.js/Node toolchain picking up the wrong
# one for apps/web instead (this is what actually happened — `next
# build`'s page-data-collection step failed with a
# "createContext is not a function" cross-React-version error until
# these two lines were removed).
public-hoist-pattern[]=@medusajs/*
